					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to refer to some transactions of the Peruṅguṟisabhā of Uttamaśīli-chaturvēdimaṅgalam. One of the fragments refers to the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Nandivarmamaṅgalam. The record is dated in the <hi rend="bold">7th regnal year</hi> (991-992 A.D.) of <hi rend="bold">Rājarājakēsarivarman</hi> i.e., <hi rend="bold">Rājarāja I.</hi> This and the following two numbers also consist of fragments of records some of which seem to have belonged to the temple at Tiruvāṉaikkā in Jambukēśvaram (see No. 16 below).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
